{"actual_usd":0.125085,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":185,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24462,"reply":"\"I don't think He was cornered into it, if that's what you mean.\" *I brush a little flour off my apron with the side of my hand, the oven giving a soft heat at my back.* \"But I don't think the cross is some extra bit of drama, either. If God means to forgive us in a way that's true clear through—without pretending evil is smaller than it is, and without leaving us outside the cost of being brought home—then the cross looks to me like mercy telling the whole truth at once.\"\n\n*I twirl that gray-threaded strand by my temple, thinking it through as the bread smell settles warm in the room.* \"A cheap pardon says, 'Never mind.' The cross says, 'I mind very much—and I'm staying to carry it.' That's different. What part is catching in you—the justice of it, or the need for blood at all?\"","rolling_24h_usd":56.35720500000002,"run_id":"68a172db-7ff1-422e-9ec7-e7306adc259a"}
